@Node "Historia programu" "Track2File.guide/Program history"

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.0  (07.07.95) - recognizes 19 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  - first release

  Recognizes headers:

  - $08090A08
  - =SB=
  - ATN! - IMP! fake
  - Ace?
  - ArcD
  - arcD
  - ArcR
  - CrM!
  - CrM2
  - Crm!
  - Crm2
  - IMP!
  - PaCK - CrM! fake
  - PP20
  - RNC1
  - RNC2
  - S404
  - XPKF
  - xVdg - Byte Killer fake

  New libraries for xfd:

  - 89A8
  - =SB=
  - Ace?
  - ArcD and arcD
  - PaCK
  - RNC1
  - RNC2
  - xVdg

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.01 (05.08.95) - recognizes 24 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  Recognizes new headers:
  - TPWM - not recognizes size of crunched file
  - ICE!
  - ATM5
  - GP
  - Dupa - IMP!

  New libraries:
  - GP
  - Dtpk
  - Dupa
  - TPWM

  Bugs removed:
  - Track2File didn't load full disk to memory i.e. first and last block
  - in file requester, pressing 'Amiga+L' caused selecting Clear instead
    of Load. Now you can use 'Amiga+O' shortcut for loading files.
  - program should work on all Amigas with MC68000 now, but decrunching
    files from odd address can crash your system.

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.02 (10.09.95) - recognizes 29 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  Recognizes new headers:
  - Ice!
  - IFT? - CrM2 fake
  - CRUN - Byte Killer fake
  - ViS1 - CrM!
  - ViSL - CrM2

  All xfd libraries were rewritten by me and some new ones were added:
  - Ice!
  - IFT?
  - CRUN
  - LOB
  - XPAC

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.03 (25.09.95) - recognizes 31 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  Added in preferences option to skip found file (skip file),
  for speed up memory scan.

  Recognizes new headers:
  - ATOM
  - Vic2

  New libraries:
  - ATOM
  - FUCK
  - JR
  - HUFF
  - Vic2

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.04 (04.10.95) - recognizes 35 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  New headers:
  - $18051973 - CrM2 fake
  - CP
  - LOB
  - VOL1

  New libraries:
  - CP
  - SSUR
  - VDCO
  - VOL1

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.05 (10.11.95) - recognizes 37 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  Added Abort gadget in information requester.

  New headers:
  - RLE
  - TITS - PP20 fake

  New libraries:
  - RLE
  - CRND

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.10 (01.12.95) - recognizes 56 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  New version recognizes 56 headers and is about @{b}35% faster!@{ub} to
  previous versions. New memory scan procedure is used. In preferences you
  can select what headers you want to search. Settings can be saved on
  disk. They will be loaded when program runs. To all decrunched and saved
  files comment will be added with information about cruncher type.

  New headers:
  - JR
  - SA
  - SC
  - SF
  - SP
  - SQ
  - CRND - Byte Killer fake
  - Dtpk - Turtle Smasher 1.32 fake
  - GC!2
  - GC!3
  - HUF#
  - KDUB - Master Cruncher 3.0 fake
  - MASM
  - MASS
  - pack
  - SFHD
  - SPv3
  - SSUR
  - VDCO

  New libraries:
  - GraftGold_Cruncher (GC!2 and GC!3)
  - KDUB
  - MASM
  - MASS
  - pack
  - SPv3

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.11 (19.12.95) - recognizes 58 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  In preferences some new gadgets was added: Deep search, Invert, Clear.
  With 'Deep search' option turned off program is about @{b}40%
  faster!@{ub} to previous version.

  New headers:
  - PaK0
  - XP10

  New libraries:
  - PaK0
  - MagneticFields (SF and SQ)

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.12 (07.01.96) - recognizes 60 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

