@EndNode

@Node "Save file" "Track2File.guide/Save file"

  Save file

  Opens file requester and saves file with given file name.

@EndNode

@Node "Decrunch & save" "Track2File.guide/Decrunch & save"

  Decrunch & save

  Decrunches file and opens file requester, then saves decrunched data.

@EndNode

@Node "Abort" "Track2File.guide/Abort"

  Abort

  Aborts memory scan.

@EndNode

@Node "Continue" "Track2File.guide/Continue"

  Continue

  Resumes memory scanning.

@EndNode

@Node "Drive to read" "Track2File.guide/Drive to read"

  Drive to read

  Changes drive to read from.

@EndNode

@Node "Converter" "Track2File.guide/Converter"

  Converter

  This command converts data on disk to the image file.

  Program supports the following data formats:
  Normal     - without comments (default).
  Graftgold  - system used in Graftgold games (reverse data order), eg.
               ViroCop ECS, Fire & Ice.
  10 of 11   - this data system uses only first 10 blocks per track (5120
               bytes instead of standard 5632 bytes). Purposed in eg. Stone
               Age.
  Pseudo OFS - this data system uses 488 bytes per block (like OFS).
               Purposed in eg. Mr.Blobby.
  Ocean      - system used in Lethal Weapon and Addams Family games. Only
               first game (RNC1) decoded, because in second game I can't
               detect any ID's.

@EndNode

@Node "Inc file name" "Track2File.guide/Inc file name"

  Inc file name

  If this gadget is activated, then after selecting 'Search' and memory
  scanning program will open file requester instead of information window.
  After entering file name, program will write found data and resume
  memory scanning. Program will append an three digit extension to
  file name, eg. if you enter file name Data, program will save files with
  names: Data.001, Data.002, etc...

@EndNode

@Node "Decrunch before save" "Track2File.guide/Decrunch before save"

  Decrunch before save

  The same as 'Inc file name', but files will be decrunched before save.

@EndNode

@Node "Skip file" "Track2File.guide/Skip file"

  Skip file

  After finding file program while resume searching from end of this file.
  If this option is disabled program while search whole this file.

@EndNode

@Node "Deep search" "Track2File.guide/Deep search"

  Deep search

  With this option turned off program scans memory by word (2 bytes), with
  turned on byte by byte.

@EndNode

@Node "RNC old" "Track2File.guide/RNC old"

  RNC old

  Program use decrunch procedure from Pro Pack V1.?? to depack files RNC1
  and RNC2.

@EndNode

@Node "Save image" "Track2File.guide/Save image"

  Save image

  Opens file requester. After selecting file name writes loaded data from
  disk to file.

@EndNode

@Node "Enable-Disable IDs" "Track2File.guide/Enable-Disable IDs"

  Enable/Disable IDs

  You can select what headers program should search.

@EndNode

@Node "Invert" "Track2File.guide/Invert"

  Invert

  Inverts selection of headers in 'Enable/Disable IDs' gadget.

@EndNode

@Node "Clear" "Track2File.guide/Clear"

  Clear

  Clears selection of headers in 'Enable/Disable IDs' gadget.

@EndNode

@Node "Save" "Track2File.guide/Save"

  Save

  Saves settings in "s:Track2File.prefs".

@EndNode

@Node "Use" "Track2File.guide/Use"

  Use

  Remebers settings.

@EndNode

@Node "Cancel" "Track2File.guide/Cancel"

  Cancel

  Returns previous settings.

@EndNode
